  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package binds two requirements whose acceptance thresholds are mutually exclusive when evaluated at the COU operating point (flow rate 5 L/min, 3000 RPM).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-primary-rh-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump",
